snippet.textDisplay: This was a very insightful video but I'm tired of people saying " i didn't have a choice". There isn't a single situation where you don't have a choice unless your autonomy has been literally compromised. Sometimes the alternate choice is difficult to make or even more difficult to even see. But at the end of the day, you gotta make the conscious decision to commit crime or gang bang. Especially since we live in the information age where there is a over abundance of role models directly at your fingertips. The cycle can't be broken if that mindset is perpetuated because it's ultimately an attempt to justify wrongdoing.

snippet.textDisplay: Not tryna hate but there is a good chance one of these dudes personally now someone who was involved in a murder of an innocent person via mistaken Identity or crossfire or just plain old trigger happy non sensical disputes where a gun was drawn and an unarmed Persons life was taken. And I really doubt if one of these dudes knew a fellow gang member who killed an innocent bystander that they would turn in their fellow gang member an give the innocent victims and their family the justice they deserve . I know it’s called can gangs co exist peacefully. But I really feel it over looks how many gang members have murdered non gang affiliated innocent bystanders . I feel like this content is only provocative to ppl who view minorities through non human stereotypes. Why should I care if gangs can co exist when there is no record of gang members turning in fellow gang members who unjustly murdered innocent non gang affiliated ppl in cold blood an yes sometimes children. This is California it’s so common that gang members shoot the wrong person . I live in Fresno an just recently a 5 yr old girl got shot in the eye at an apartment complex that has a bit of a reputation for housing gang members . An even a few years back a 9 yr old girl got shot to death by gang members in crossfire . I know if gangs get along it saves bystander lives but I just don’t know why I should empathize w them when they continually show a disregard for the lives of the general public including innocent bystanders and children . I’m really not tryna hate. I feel like this content is used to humanize their experience and lives. But I already view them as ppl who had to endure challenges I would have failed at. But in spite of that the reality is they are a part of a culture that has taken numerous lives of non gang affiliated ppl and by the rules of their culture they won’t bring the shooter of the innocent ppl to justice because that would be considered cooperating with the authorities. Point is gang members hella shoot innocent ppl and other gang members protect those secrets and that’s fucked up . So it’s hard to empathize . Like some California gang members literally try to have the mentality of o dog from the movie . I know tht sounds corny but if u really unpack that then I think you’ll get the point I’m tryin to make I’m not tryna hate seriously

I gained a lot of respect for these people!
